Staging (Staging Table) is a temporary table where raw data is first loaded before processing it into the final tables. 

Assignments

1) Join Customer and Fact table 

SELECT c.CUSTOMER_NAME, c.CITY, 
    SUM(F.AMOUNT) AS TOTAL_REVENUE, 
    COUNT(F.ORDER_ID) AS TOTAL_ORDERS,
    CASE
        WHEN SUM(F.AMOUNT) > 20000 THEN 'PLATINUM'
        WHEN SUM(F.AMOUNT) > 10000 THEN 'GOLD'
        ELSE 'SILVER'
    END AS REVENUE_CATEGORY
    FROM DIM_CUSTOMER c
    JOIN FACT_ORDERS F
        ON C.CUSTOMER_ID = F.CUSTOMER_ID
    GROUP BY c.CUSTOMER_NAME, c.CITY;        # Group all rows by each customer and city, then calculate SUM and COUNT for each group
    
    # GROUP BY is used to group rows that have same values
        so that we can apply aggregate functions like:
        SUM(),COUNT(),AVG(),MAX(),MIN()  

2) Top 3 customers per city using row_number 

SELECT *
FROM(
SELECT C.CUSTOMER_NAME, C.CITY,
       SUM(F.AMOUNT) AS TOTAL_REVENUE,
     ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY CITY
    ORDER BY SUM(AMOUNT)DESC) AS ROW_NUMBER
   FROM DIM_CUSTOMER C
   JOIN FACT_ORDERS F
   ON C.CUSTOMER_ID = F.CUSTOMER_ID
   GROUP BY C.CUSTOMER_NAME, C.CITY)
   WHERE ROW_NUMBER <=3;

3) Create a view
A view is a virtual table created from a SELECT query
It does NOT store data
It stores only the query
Every time you query the view, it runs the underlying SELECT

    CREATE VIEW view_name AS
    SELECT column1, column2
    FROM table_name
    WHERE condition;

       
CREATE VIEW VW_ACTIVE_CUSTOMER_REVENUE AS
    SELECT c.CUSTOMER_NAME, c.CITY,
           SUM(f.AMOUNT) AS TOTAL_REVENUE,
           COUNT(f.ORDER_ID) AS TOTAL_ORDERS,
           CASE
               WHEN SUM(f.AMOUNT) > 20000 THEN 'PLATINUM'
               WHEN SUM(f.AMOUNT) > 10000 THEN 'GOLD'
               ELSE 'SILVER'
           END AS REVENUE_CATEGORY
    FROM DIM_CUSTOMER c
    JOIN FACT_ORDERS f
    ON c.CUSTOMER_ID = f.CUSTOMER_ID
    WHERE c.IS_ACTIVE = TRUE
    GROUP BY c.CUSTOMER_NAME,c.CITY
    HAVING COUNT(F.ORDER_ID) > 2
       AND SUM(f.AMOUNT) > 5000;

    SELECT*FROM VW_ACTIVE_CUSTOMER_REVENUE;

